'''''Star Wars: The Legacy Revealed''''' is a [[Wikipedia:Documentary film|documentary]] about the impact the original [[1977]] ''[[Star Wars]]'' film has had upon society and filmmaking, with a focus on the place of the series in the continuum of cultural mythology. The two-hour program debuted on [[Wikipedia:The History Channel|The History Channel]] on [[May 28]], [[2007]], coinciding roughly with the 30-year anniversary of ''Star Wars''. It featured interviews with journalists, filmmakers, critics, academic experts, and politicians, including [[Wikipedia:Newt Gingrich|Newt Gingrich]], [[Wikipedia:Tom Brokaw|Tom Brokaw]], [[J.J. Abrams]], [[Wikipedia:Peter Jackson|Peter Jackson]], [[Kevin Smith]], [[Wikipedia:Joss Whedon|Joss Whedon]], [[Wikipedia:Dan Rather|Dan Rather]], and [[Wikipedia:Nancy Pelosi|Nancy Pelosi]].

It was the #1 highest rated History Channel program among viewers aged 18-49, and #2 among viewers aged 25-54,<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.theforce.net/latestnews/story/Star_Wars_The_Legacy_Revealed_Ratings_News_106378.asp|text=Star Wars: The Legacy Revealed Ratings News|author=Barrick, Mike|date=2007-05-21|archivedate=20190730080146}}</ref> and was nominated for three Emmy awards.<ref name="SWArchive-Three Emmy Noms for Star Wars: The Legacy Revealed">{{SWArchive|url=community/news/media/news20070719.html|text=Three Emmy Noms for ''Star Wars'': The Legacy Revealed}}</ref>

